&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct answer is, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;option 1)&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The position of the letters according to the English alphabet series:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/05/alphabet.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 559px; height: 149px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The logic that follows here is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sum of the positional value of the corresponding alphabet.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SO is written as 34&amp;nbsp;&amp;rArr; S(19) + O(15) = 34&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BED is written as 11&amp;nbsp;&amp;rArr; B(2) + E(5) + D(4) = 11&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Similarly,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MOAN&lt;/strong&gt; is written as 43&amp;nbsp;&amp;rArr; M(13) + O(15) + A(1) + N(14) = 43&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;option 1)&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;According to the English alphabet&amp;nbsp;and their positional values:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/qImage102.png&quot; style=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The pattern followed in the given codes is:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;The alphabet at odd places are increased by&amp;nbsp;1 positional value.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The alphabet at even places are decreased by&amp;nbsp;1 positional value.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;JACCUZI&amp;rsquo; is written as &amp;lsquo;KZDBVYJ&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/qImage15299.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;lsquo;QUIZZER&amp;rsquo; is written as &amp;lsquo;RTJYADS&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/qImage15300.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Similarly,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;lsquo;BUZZWIG&amp;rsquo;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is written as&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;CTAYXHH&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/qImage15301.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;the correct answer is option 2).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We compare the given codes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/12/F1_Mrunal_SSC_10.12.2022_D133.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 351px; height: 114px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can see that &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;can&amp;#39; is coded as &amp;#39;sent&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;the correct answer is option 2)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The position of the letters according to the English alphabet series:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/05/alphabet.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 559px; height: 149px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The logic followed here is shown below:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The letter GOA is written as 7151. i.e&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;G &amp;rArr;7; O &amp;rArr;15; A &amp;rArr;1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the same way, DOG is written as 4157, i.e&lt;/p&gt;

